# S10-T01: Safe Area Foundation

## Objective
Port NaviTrack safe-area patterns so the MuseCool gradient fills the notch/status bar and
content respects insets on all orientations.

## Reference audit (read-only)
Study these NaviTrack files — do not copy dark-theme tokens:
- `src/styles/layout.css` — body `padding-bottom: env(safe-area-inset-bottom)`, `#root` flex column, `100dvh`
- `src/styles/touch.css` — `.safe-top`, `.safe-bottom`, `.safe-bottom-pwa`
- `src/styles/screen-layout.css` — landscape `--pwa-spacing-x/r` horizontal insets
- `index.html` — `viewport-fit=cover`, `interactive-widget=resizes-content`

## Acceptance Criteria
- No white band above ScorePanel on iPhone simulator (portrait + landscape).
- Background gradient visible under status bar (html/body extend full viewport).
- Screen roots use `.safe-top` (or equivalent) so glass panels sit below notch.
- Piano keybed keeps bottom safe inset; landscape adds horizontal inset on content column.
- S01 colour tokens unchanged; only layout/safe-area CSS added.

## Steps
1. Add safe-area utilities to `musecool/src/index.css` (mirror NaviTrack naming).
2. Update `index.css` base: html/body min-height `100dvh`, overscroll-behavior, body safe-bottom.
3. Apply `.safe-top` to app shell / ScorePanel wrapper; landscape horizontal padding on screen roots.
4. Verify `index.html` viewport meta matches NaviTrack (`interactive-widget=resizes-content` optional).
5. Test iPhone 16e + SE simulators portrait/landscape — screenshot before/after.
6. `git commit -m "fix(pwa): safe-area foundation from NaviTrack pattern"`.
